A GLASGOW <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Researcher" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Researcher" target="_blank">researcher</a> has found the oldest surviving nonbiblical <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript" target="_blank">manuscript</a> in ScotlandThe 12th century copy of the â<a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Consolation_of_Philosophy" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Consolation_of_Philosophy" target="_blank">Consolation of Philosophy</a>â by <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boethius" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boethius" target="_blank">Boethius</a> a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Statesman" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Statesman" target="_blank">statesman</a> of the late Roman Empire was <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_Ages" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_Ages" target="_blank">Medieval Europe</a>'s bestknown <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intellectual" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intellectual" target="_blank">intellectual</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Textbook" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Textbook" target="_blank">text</a> second only to the BibleIt discusses <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Free_will" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Free_will" target="_blank">freewill</a> fate the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Idea" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Idea" target="_blank">idea</a> of the wheel of fortune in a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meditation" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meditation" target="_blank">meditation</a> and how to cope with adversity and injustice <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boethius" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boethius" target="_blank">Boethius</a> is <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thought" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thought" target="_blank">thought</a> to have <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Writing" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Writing" target="_blank">written</a> the original in 524AD when he was awaiting <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Capital_punishment" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Capital_punishment" target="_blank">execution</a> for a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crime_fiction" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crime_fiction" target="_blank">crime</a> he didn't commitDr Kylie <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murray_Rothbard" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murray_Rothbard" target="_blank">Murray</a> made the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Discovery_Channel" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Discovery_Channel" target="_blank">discovery</a> in the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Glasgow" target="_blank">University of Glasgow</a>'s Special Collections where she is visiting from <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Balliol_College,_Oxford" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Balliol_College,_Oxford" target="_blank">Balliol College</a> OxfordThe <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boethius" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boethius" target="_blank">Boethius</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript" target="_blank">manuscript</a> had <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bengali_language" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bengali_language" target="_blank">ben</a> catalogued but was believed to be <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_studies" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_studies" target="_blank">English</a> putting <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durham_University" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durham_University" target="_blank">Durham</a> as the likely <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Original_sin" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Original_sin" target="_blank">origin</a> But closer examination found the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Handwriting" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Handwriting" target="_blank">handwriting</a> and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illustration" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illustration" target="_blank">illustrations</a> didn't match those in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durham_University" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durham_University" target="_blank">Durham</a> or other <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_studies" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_studies" target="_blank">English</a> textsDr <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murray_Rothbard" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murray_Rothbard" target="_blank">Murray</a> said the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript" target="_blank">manuscript</a>'s unique <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illustration" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illustration" target="_blank">illustrations</a> more closely resemble the famous Kelso <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charter" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charter" target="_blank">Charter</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Writing" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Writing" target="_blank">written</a> at Kelso Abbey in 1159 She said Dr <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murray_Rothbard" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murray_Rothbard" target="_blank">Murray</a> said â<a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Glasgow" target="_blank">Glasgow</a>'s <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boethius" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boethius" target="_blank">Boethius</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript" target="_blank">manuscript</a> allows a fresh <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Understanding" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Understanding" target="_blank">understanding</a> of <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/